node.text: Until just recently, Vancouver Island’s landmass was almost entirely old-growth rainforest, yet only about 10% remains today thanks to industrial logging. These old trees play a critical role in boosting a forest’s immunity – when we lose them, we lose the blueprint of an entire ecosystem’s resilience. We cannot level what took hundreds, even thousands, of years for nature to perfect and expect it ever to recover, so we need your help. Governments and large corporations feel secure making harmful environmental decisions when allowed to operate in the shadows, often taking special measures to prevent the public from becoming aware of their actions. Well, we can see them now, and we are not about to let them get away with it. Please visit the link in my bio and urge BC officials to protect the last of our old-growth forests before it is too late. Video by @ReelWater. With @FairyCreekBlockade. #FairyCreekBlockade #FairyCreek #VancouverIsland #BC #BritishColumbia #Canada #Logging #Trees #Forests #AncientForests #OldGrowth #SaveOldGrowth #SaveOldGrowthNow #SaveFairyCreek #Conservation

node.text: 🔊 Please turn up your volume to learn about Timor-Leste's incredible marine ecosystems and get a behind-the-scenes look at our encounter with a magnificent blue whale. Looking into the eye of the largest animal that has ever lived on our planet and seeing them stare back was an experience that changed me forever. I have been fortunate enough to visit many unique locations, and I have seen some wonderful things in my career, but there are only a handful of memories I'll think about on my deathbed. This is one of them. The cobalt waters of Timor-Leste are abundant with an incredible variety of life, making responsible, sustainable ecotourism an ideal way for local communities to support themselves. Our objective at @sealegacy and @onlyone is to share the beauty and wonder of these faraway places so people everywhere will be inspired to stand up and protect them from the threat of climate change and other human-made issues. Please consider visiting the link in my bio and supporting our conservation mission by joining The Tide today. On expedition for @sealegacy in Timor-Leste with @mitty, @andy_mann, and @sonyalpha. #ShotOnSony #SonyAlpha #BeAlpha #whale #bluewhale #timorleste #life #beauty #conservation #bucketlist

node.text: There’s only one thing in wildlife and nature photography that really matters, and that’s the moment. Every situation that unfolds in front of me is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to tell a story that can connect a global audience to the most important issues facing our planet. There is always more than just my creative vision to consider, especially underwater – am I weighted properly, is everything working, where are the other divers, where are the other sharks. But if I can shoot 8K video and 50 MP stills with the same tool, I have one less thing to worry about and am free to go off and be an artist. Conservation and storytelling are my passions – it is a pleasure to have partners that make it easier to succeed. node.text: 🔊 // Congratulations to @sonyalpha on the launch of their new α1 camera – please turn up your volume and enjoy this beautiful video about an epic milestone in photography. I am especially excited because innovation like this results in an enhanced ability to do our conservation work better than ever before. As always, I am incredibly grateful to have a sponsor and partner that provides us with the best tools in the world to tell the planet's most important stories. #sony #sonyalpha #a1 #bealpha

node.text: The Galápagos is an invaluable and irreplaceable treasure of our ocean – a truly legendary World Heritage Site that is a refuge for 3,000 marine species. Yet, industrial and unsustainable fishing practices continue to plunder its waters and devastate its fragile ecosystem thanks to inaction from a government that has pledged to protect it. Please visit the link in my bio where you can show your support for additional protections by signing our petition – we need your help to ensure Ecuadorian President @leninmorenog and President of the National Assembly @cesarlitardo fulfill their commitment to expanding the Galápagos Marine Reserve before any further damage is done. With @onlyone and @sealegacy. @mas_galapagos2020 #masgalapagos #yoestoycongalapagos #galapagos #ecuador #gratitude

node.text: Today is @mitty's birthday. I am so fortunate and thankful to have a partner in life who not only matches my passion but magnifies it. Cristina is a caring mother, talented diver, fearless explorer, gifted photographer, and tireless conservationist. She is wise and kind, and leads with a gentle heart. She makes everyone around her better, myself included. Please consider celebrating her birthday with me by visiting the link in my bio and joining The Tide to support our conservation mission at @sealegacy and our activation platform, @onlyone – 100% of your contribution will go directly to projects and campaigns to rebuild marine life. As always, thank you for standing with us to protect the world's oceans – your support means the world to all of us. Feel free to leave a birthday message for her below, and I'll be sure she sees them. #onlyoneocean #birthday #partner #inspiration #luckyguy

node.text: The fjords of northern Norway are unlike any place on Earth. I have visited several times during my career and captured many of my proudest images there. Now, talk of seismic oil and gas exploration threatens to put Lofoten's enormous orca population at risk. I am excited to announce the upcoming @onlyone screening of our new short documentary film, 'Echoes in the Arctic,' on Tuesday, November 10th, at 7 pm ET (4 pm PT). Filmmakers @mitty, @andymaser, @tahriasheather, and I will be sticking around afterward for a live Q&A, so be sure to RSVP at the link in my bio – hope to see you there. #onlyoneocean #orca #lofoten #norway #documentary #filmmaking #climatechange #conservation #storytelling

node.text: 🔊 // Art and storytelling have sparked many beautiful relationships in my career, but few are as meaningful as this one. I have spent countless evenings sifting through my image library with @thelumineers blasting in the background, so to discover that @jeremiahfraites, co-founder of my favourite band, had one of my fine art pieces hanging on his wall was a wonderful surprise. Soon after connecting, I discovered we had much more in common than a healthy appreciation for each other's art. Jeremiah and his wife, @francesca_laz, are avid conservationists who care deeply about the same bears in Katmai, Alaska, that I have been obsessed with ever since photographing them in 1991, long before my @natgeo days. He recently sent me a demo of "Maggie" after divulging his upcoming solo project, and I instantly recognized it as an opportunity to collaborate. Today, I am proud to share the music video we crafted together. Most of this footage has never been seen outside the @sealegacy walls – it is a tribute to the intelligent, majestic, and vulnerable brown bears of Alaska. Together, we hope our art will inspire you to join us in a stand against the Pebble Mine development that threatens to wipe out their habitat. The time for action is now – visit the link in my bio to send a message to Senator Sullivan, Senator Murkowski, and the EPA today. Filmed on assignment for @sealegacy with @andymaser, @samkretch, and @kyle.roepke. #jeremiahfraites #thelumineers #maggie #pianopiano #newmusic #bear #brownbear #katmai #bristolbay #alaska #pebblemine #stoppebblemine #vetopebblemine #nopebblemine #shareyourbears #thinkaboutbears #art #collaboration #conservation #passion

node.text: 🔊 Please turn up your volume and come on a journey with me to witness the remarkable coastal wolves of British Columbia. // I am really proud of our small but mighty @sealegacy team when I see them create powerful and impactful storytelling pieces. Please watch the entire film and let me know your thoughts. @sealegacy and our partners at @raincoastconservation have a plan to end the commercial trophy hunting of wolves, bears, and wolverines in British Columbia’s Kitlope Conservancy permanently, but we need your help. Two very generous patrons have just confirmed they will donation-match half of the final $100,000 needed to buy up the remaining hunting licenses in the area, which would double the impact of your contribution. A good friend of mine and avid supporter of @sealegacy just came in for $20K. Please visit the link in my bio if you want to get involved in pushing this protection over the finish line so we can save this community of wolves. 🙏💙 Shot on assignment for @sealegacy with @johnkelseyphoto. Audio and BTS clips by @maxwelhohn, @steve_woods_photography, and @seaforthexpeditions. node.text: 🔊 Sound on to hear @mitty tell the beautiful story of the Mermaids of Atauro – I couldn't resist lifting it from her account to share with all of you. I am always in awe of how easily she connects with people on expedition. Her energy is infectious, kind, and gentle – people invite her into their worlds the same way animals let me into theirs. It helps that she speaks several languages, Portuguese in this case. Next month, we board our boat and set off on assignment with the @sealegacy team to unearth more moments like this. In the meantime, click my bio link to sign up for @onlyone and watch more from "The Last Coral Kingdom" series on our 30x30 journey. // Reposted from @mitty: "'Obrigada pela natureza.' The song drifted across the sea from a woman moving waist-deep in the shallows of Timor-Leste, her voice rising gently with the rolling swells. I knew instantly who she was and waded out to her from shore, tears welling in my eyes as I recognized the meaning behind the Portuguese words. Spanning around her in a wide circle were a handful of tiny boats trailing baited hooks through the water, an ingenious fishing technique I had never seen before used by the Wawata Tapu; the Mermaids of Auturo. As I drew close, she smiled brightly and sang again, "Obrigada pela natureza, hallelujah!" A fisherwoman's hymn giving thanks to nature for providing for her family. A surge of hope flooded through me, and in that moment, I wanted the world to meet Sara. Today, you finally can." // With @samkretch, @andy_mann, and @mitty on assignment for @sealegacy. #onlyoneocean #30x30 #thelastcoralkingdom #mermaidsofauturo #timorleste

node.text: A dear friend of mine, @AmiVitale, has recently completed a gorgeous film titled 'Shaba' – the story of a young elephant rescued by the Reteti Elephant Sanctuary staff after poachers shot and killed her mother. I had the opportunity to see these iconic animals in the wild for the first time when I visited Kenya in 2017, and I returned home with a new respect for the organizations working overtime to save them from poachers and other serious threats. I invite you to visit the link in my bio and watch 'Shaba' on-demand before August 31st – tickets are by donation, and all proceeds benefit the elephants at @R.E.S.C.U.E, Africa's first indigenous-owned and operated elephant sanctuary, by funding the purchase of milk, blankets, medicines, and more. It is an incredible initiative led by a passionate group of conservationists, and I am proud to offer my support. Video by @AmiVitale. With @SararaFoundation, @ConservationOrg, @KenyaWildlifeService, @NRT_Kenya, and @Tusk_Org. #ShabaFilm #Shaba #RetetiElephantSanctuary #Elephants #Kenya #Africa #SaveElephants #StopPoaching

node.text: I am very pleased to announce that I am one of a hundred hand-selected artists, activists, journalists, scientists, and thought-leaders who have partnered with Facebook to be part of Bulletin – a brand new platform for long-form content. It has always been challenging to relate my experiences as a photographer, filmmaker, and conservationist within an Instagram caption. I am excited to finally have a place where I can share every detail of my favorite moments from the field, the philosophy behind my fine art, lessons I have learned from a lifetime in the company of wild animals, and more. My first article is the story behind the exact moment I decided what to do with my life, and it is live right now. Please visit the link in my bio to read it for yourself and subscribe to my feed, where I will be sharing many more stories and insights over the coming weeks and months. #Orca #Lofoton #Norway #Stories #Storytelling #Facebook #Bulletin #Platform #Launch #Welcome #Subscribe #Gratitude

node.text: ⁠#LimitedEditionPrint // The sun never fully broke the horizon during @SeaLegacy's two-week expedition to the majestic fjords of Northern Norway. I was lucky to freeze this large male orca, truly one of the most impressive apex predators ever to evolve, as he exploded through the glassy surface with only a hint of pink morning light on the horizon. I knew he was watching us, a group of strange, helpless animals who were barely able to keep up, and couldn't help but feel inferior. Riding alongside him made the arrogance of placing ourselves on the highest pillar of the podium of species obvious. 'Dawn Patrol,' and other similar content we captured on this expedition, played a key role in keeping big oil out of Norway's pristine Arctic ecosystem in what was a major win for conservation. Many thanks to my good friend, @GoraneHlme, without whom it would not have been possible. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #Orca #NorthernFjords #Norway #ApexPredator #PodiumOfSpecies #Conservation

node.text: ⁠#LimitedEditionPrint // I rarely opt for slow shutter speeds when photographing wildlife, but opening myself up to the unexpected by playing with light or going against the traditional rules of composition almost always yields an interesting result. 'The Waiting Game' is a good example. I remember feeling a ton of pressure to produce images for @NatGeo during my spirit bear assignment. Having run out of light for the day, I had to choose between packing it in or trading my telephoto lens for something shorter mounted to a tripod and attempting two-second exposures. I took hundreds of images before one worked out, and the resulting blurred water created a moody feeling I would never have captured otherwise. It was a waiting game worth playing. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #Bear #SpiritBear #KermodeBear #BC #BritishColumbia #Canada #WaitingGame #SlowShutter #ExpectTheUnexpected

node.text: #LimitedEditionPrint // On rare occasions during southern expeditions, I would escape the confines of our vessel for an evening and cruise amongst Antarctica's towering ice giants in a little Zodiac. Like the forgotten ruins of some ancient civilization, the frozen monuments in 'Grounded' are a disappearing testament to nature's extraordinary glacial architecture. There is a story behind every scar, furrow, and crack in the ice – my job is to bring them home and share them with all of you so we can change the narrative together before our clock runs out. // To inquire about this piece or view my entire fine art catalog, please visit the link in my bio. #FineArt #LimitedEdition #Iceberg #IcebergAlley #Antarctica #ClimateChange #Conservation #Story #Narrative #RewriteTheFuture

node.text: This post is simply to say thank you. THANK YOU!! Thank you to everyone who joined The Tide this week and shared our @SeaLegacy campaign across your social media channels – you made me nearly fall out of my chair yesterday, and that was before I saw the likes of @Jennifer.Garner, @hollyrpeete, @ryanepeete @AlecBaldwinInsta, @ChrissyMetz, @RachieSkarsten, @robertirwinphotography,@SarahWayneCallies, and others join in. Many of my close friends at @NatGeo shared our content as well – you are too numerous to list, but I thank every single one of you for all you do. To see this level of dedication and passion for ocean conservation filled me with more hope than I have experienced in quite some time. I was blown away – it officially became the most wonderful birthday ever. To be honest, we had bets going on in our office about how many people would join The Tide. Some predicted we would gain as few as a hundred new members, but I have witnessed your passion, support, and engagement in the past, so I predicted the highest number of anyone on our team at five hundred new members. It turns out I was wrong too – we gained six hundred 620 new Tide Members, and that number is still climbing. Our Tide Community is now more than 7000 members strong, mostly made up of folks who donate to ocean conservation with small-dollar contributions. The best part is that the donations go directly towards ocean solutions. Now, be ready to come on a journey with us and be part of a very exciting and hopeful mission.  #BestBirthdayEver #Gratitude

node.text: A pair of four-month-old polar bear cubs peek out from behind their mother as she rests on the sea ice near Ellesmere Island, Nunavut. At this stage in their development, each cub consumes just under 500g of her incredibly rich milk per day, which has a fat content of 20-40% compared to the 3-5% that humans produce. She must regularly catch seals while conserving as much of her own energy as possible to maintain this output, so travel is limited to nighttime when the snow is firmer and the air is cooler. #Bear #PolarBear #EllesmereIsland #Nunavut #Canada #Cubs #Mother #Milk #Energy #Survival #Conservation

Hello everyone! It’s @Mitty, and I’m taking over @PaulNicklen’s account for his birthday! I invite you to celebrate Paul with me and help us save the ocean by visiting the link in his bio and joining The Tide! If you join us before 11:59 pm ET on July 25th, you’ll be entered to win Paul’s @ZodiacWatches Super Sea Wolf 53. See only.one/giveaway-rules for eligibility.⁠
⁠
Recently, I asked him what he most wanted for his birthday this year. Without hesitation, he replied: “I wish I could just save the ocean.” I know the feeling, as I am keenly aware that saving the ocean offers us the biggest bang for our buck when it comes to building resilience and putting a dent in the massive dual threats of climate change and biodiversity loss. We don’t have a magic wand, but we know that through the power of our will and voices demanding action and investing in solutions, we can make the greatest impact. We know because we have the conservation victories to prove it! That is why we created The Tide, a global community of action-takers from all races, genders, and walks of life, and we have room for more. You can be part of Paul’s 53rd journey around the sun, and you can help us turn the tide. So what are you waiting for? Please join us in building a healthier world for all. #Lynx #NorthwestTerritories #Canada #Birthday #Conservation #Contest #EnterToWin #ZodiacWatches #SuperSeaWolf53 #TheTide #TurningTheTide

node.text: For my birthday this year, I want you to get involved with our conservation movement by joining The Tide. Our work at @SeaLegacy depends on the support of our Tide members – the more of us there are, the greater the impact we are able to make. As a thank you to everyone who contributes to our mission, we’re having a contest where I'll be giving away the @ZodiacWatches Super Sea Wolf 53 I wore while filming sharks, rays, and other iconic species in The Bahamas over these last nine months. If you would like a chance to win it for yourself, simply visit the link in my bio and join The Tide (or submit your entry) before 11:59 pm ET on July 25th. Existing Tide members will be entered automatically. See only.one/giveaway-rules for eligibility. Good luck! #Birthday #Conservation #Contest #EnterToWin #ZodiacWatches #SuperSeaWolf53 #TheTide #TurningTheTide
